SIMPLE: moreover
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Moreover
<hw>More*o"ver</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <ety>[<ets>More</ets>
+ <ets>over</ets>.]</ety> <def>Beyond what has been said; further;
besides; in addition; furthermore; also; likewise.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Moreover</qex>, he hath left you all his walks.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- <er>Besides</er>, <er>Moreover</er>.</syn>
<usage> Of the two words, <xex>moreover</xex> is the stronger and is
properly used in solemn discourse, or when what is added is important to
be considered. See <er>Besides</er>.</usage>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Morepork</ent>⟦br⟧
